This paper is about improving the efficiency and performance of deep reinforcement learning algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on prioritizing sequences of experience, which involves both learning from past experiences (cs.AI) and optimizing the agent's decision-making process (cs.RO). The experiments conducted in the paper involve using deep Q-learning networks to play Atari games, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.SY) as it requires the agent to interpret visual input and make decisions based on that input.
